      "content": "Using lubricating eye drops is generally safe for soothing dryness, but it might mask a more serious underlying problem. If the cause is something like conjunctivitis or an infection, the drops won't clear it up and could potentially delay necessary treatment. Relying only on drops might prevent you from getting the correct diagnosis for the redness and pain you are experiencing. Please try to schedule a quick appointment soon to ensure your eye gets the right care.",
